{"abstract": "We propose a deep learning-based approach to the problem of premise selection: selecting mathematical statements relevant for proving a given conjecture. We represent a higher-order logic formula as a graph that is invariant to variable renaming but still fully preserves syntactic and semantic information. We then embed the graph into a vector via a novel embedding method that preserves the information of edge ordering. Our approach achieves state-of-the-art results on the HolStep dataset, improving the classification accuracy from 83% to 90.3%.", "referenced_work_ids": ["f1318d15d7d8ab626b92d0c70dbdc5b5d37e223f", "e77e00286a63a32dafb9629cd79f6a77bddb1941", "2651ce8012ac95b5c962068aa239913d65be2244", "bf4dc8112c00cddd87c5f6110dae5efc305b1a27", "36eff562f65125511b5dfab68ce7f7a943c27478", "2ab3c53b08d4180c8642207ee09738f8df193b92", "36ee2c8bd605afd48035d15fdc6b8c8842363376", "c41eb895616e453dcba1a70c9b942c5063cc656c", "f8909e8b359c72bc0e3257dadcc48a8787bca74b", "b863c56ecdc03a7edbcf702c6e34b2db70eba219", "7c6de5a9e02a779e24504619050c6118f4eac181", "b4f6c3858f2c6dd37e3e89fbe1453a3390e8e4ac", "44e1ee7a63a01a76371d7070c132361a5ddd54a0", "492f57ee9ceb61fb5a47ad7aebfec1121887a175", "5d1bfeed240709725c78bc72ea40e55410b373dc", "e49ff72d420c8d72e62a9353e3abc053445e59bd", "0834e74304b547c9354b6d7da6fa78ef47a48fa8", "32de44f01a96d4473d21099d15e25bc2b9f08e2f", "995c5f5e62614fcb4d2796ad2faab969da51713e", "de5eff4b6c605fa7318adfef99f5705416153a7b", "fff114cbba4f3ba900f33da574283e3de7f26c83", "19169c6de54bfb3b06a6a16e593cdf7ac1391209", "87f40e6f3022adbc1f1905e3e506abad05a9964f", "d284b03bea04349b1e7ad4aa72b4defab2f13e1c", "6770570a45fe0fa38000e2465f8338604da7f312", "76ad9a7e9a9a047adb533a150c98c2a0c5fe9cc9", "f6b51c8753a871dc94ff32152c00c01e94f90f09", "542b7e88597f255c3b91e6254ce1c8dd3e820375", "ae5e6c6f5513613a161b2c85563f9708bf2e9178", "91ab9a65e276cff7f62c7279dd507967804c2477", "4b3d5711c5d38b1a00e73de359f910a13de610a5", "9c0ddf74f87d154db88d79c640578c1610451eec", 